Every time you start a new html project, you have to configure a couple things over and over. When you have some standard configurations at hand, this could be an enormous time saver and can avoid easily made mistakes at deploy stage! A good example is HTML/CSS/JS-kickstart.

Through the hand of time, we’ve created something alike, because there isn’t something like “the perfect starting files”. And after all, everyone has other needs and preferences. You can easily make one yourself too!

Read the full manual here: 
http://blog.mrhenry.be/2009/07/speed-up-your-html-development/